            <q>Calls for government to underwrite the Pension Protection Fund have been described as 'outrageous' by its inaugural chairman, Lawrence Churchill".</q>
            The matter has not been decided by this House or by Parliament generally. I have to say that that seems wholly inappropriate.
          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0664P0-00950'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0664P0_20040719_GCR_203' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        It is possible for the Government to make appointments provided that a Bill has had a Second Reading in the other place, which this Bill has. But it seems quite wrong for someone appointed in such circumstances&#x2014;the legislation is not completed and it is possible that it will never be completed&#x2014;to intervene as apparently he has. I hope very much that the Government will look into the matter. Perhaps the
        
        <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_31gc' title='Col. 31GC &mdash; HL Deb 19 July 2004 vol 664 c31GC' name='column_31gc' href='#column_31gc' rel='bookmark'>31GC</a>
        Minister will tell us what has happened at our next meeting. Does she agree that, if the report is correct, it is inappropriate to make that kind of remark?
      </p>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0664P0-00951'>
        <a name='S5LV0664P0_20040719_GCR_204'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/ms-patricia-hollis' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
